casadi::Nlpsol Class Referenceabstract

NLP solver storage class. More...

#include <nlpsol_impl.hpp>

Detailed Description

Author
Joel Andersson
Date
2010-2013


List of available options
IdTypeDescriptionUsed in
ad_weightOT_DOUBLEWeighting factor for derivative calculation.When there is an option of either using forward or reverse mode directional derivatives, the condition ad_weight*nf<=(1-ad_weight)*na is used where nf and na are estimates of the number of forward/reverse mode directional derivatives needed. By default, ad_weight is calculated automatically, but this can be overridden by setting this option. In particular, 0 means forcing forward mode and 1 forcing reverse mode. Leave unset for (class specific) heuristics.casadi::FunctionInternal
ad_weight_spOT_DOUBLEWeighting factor for sparsity pattern calculation calculation.Overrides default behavior. Set to 0 and 1 to force forward and reverse mode respectively. Cf. option "ad_weight".casadi::FunctionInternal
compilerOT_STRINGJust-in-time compiler plugin to be used.casadi::FunctionInternal
derivative_ofOT_FUNCTIONThe function is a derivative of another function. The type of derivative (directional derivative, Jacobian) is inferred from the function name.casadi::FunctionInternal
eval_errors_fatalOT_BOOLWhen errors occur during evaluation of f,g,...,stop the iterationscasadi::Nlpsol
expandOT_BOOLReplace MX with SX expressions in problem formulation [false]casadi::Nlpsol
gather_statsOT_BOOLFlag to indicate whether statistics must be gatheredcasadi::FunctionInternal
ignore_check_vecOT_BOOLIf set to true, the input shape of F will not be checked.casadi::Nlpsol
input_schemeOT_STRINGVECTORCustom input schemecasadi::FunctionInternal
inputs_checkOT_BOOLThrow exceptions when the numerical values of the inputs don't make sensecasadi::FunctionInternal
iteration_callbackOT_FUNCTIONA function that will be called at each iteration with the solver as input. Check documentation of Callback.casadi::Nlpsol
iteration_callback_ignore_errorsOT_BOOLIf set to true, errors thrown by iteration_callback will be ignored.casadi::Nlpsol
iteration_callback_stepOT_INTOnly call the callback function every few iterations.casadi::Nlpsol
jac_penaltyOT_DOUBLEWhen requested for a number of forward/reverse directions, it may be cheaper to compute first the full jacobian and then multiply with seeds, rather than obtain the requested directions in a straightforward manner. Casadi uses a heuristic to decide which is cheaper. A high value of 'jac_penalty' makes it less likely for the heurstic to chose the full Jacobian strategy. The special value -1 indicates never to use the full Jacobian strategycasadi::FunctionInternal
jitOT_BOOLUse just-in-time compiler to speed up the evaluationcasadi::FunctionInternal
jit_optionsOT_DICTOptions to be passed to the jit compiler.casadi::FunctionInternal
monitorOT_STRINGVECTORMonitors to be activatedcasadi::FunctionInternal
output_schemeOT_STRINGVECTORCustom output schemecasadi::FunctionInternal
print_timeOT_BOOLprint information about execution timecasadi::Nlpsol
regularity_checkOT_BOOLThrow exceptions when NaN or Inf appears during evaluationcasadi::FunctionInternal
user_dataOT_VOIDPTRA user-defined field that can be used to identify the function or pass additional informationcasadi::FunctionInternal
verboseOT_BOOLVerbose evaluation – for debuggingcasadi::FunctionInternal
verbose_initOT_BOOLPrint out timing information about the different stages of initializationcasadi::Nlpsol
warn_initial_boundsOT_BOOLWarn if the initial guess does not satisfy LBX and UBXcasadi::Nlpsol

1531  }

1536  }

1540  for (int i=0; i<n_in; ++i) {

1543  i_names.push_back(ss.str());
1544  }
1545  }
1546

1548  std::vector<std::string> o_names;
1549  o_names.reserve(n_out*nfwd);
1550

1552  for (int d=0; d<nfwd; ++d) {
1553  for (int i=0; i<n_out; ++i) {
1554  ss.str(string());
1555  ss << "fwd" << d << "_" << oscheme_.at(i);
1556  o_names.push_back(ss.str());
1557  }
1558  }

1575  i<n_in+n_out ? sparsity_out(i-n_in) :
1576  sparsity_in((i-n_in-n_out) % n_in);

1579  << i_names.at(i) << "\". Expected " << sp.size()
1580  << " but got " << ret.size_in(i));
1581  }
1582 
1583  // Consistency check for outputs
1584  for (int i=0; i<ret.n_out(); ++i) {
1585  const Sparsity& sp = sparsity_out(i % n_out);
1586  casadi_assert_message(ret.size_out(i)==sp.size(),

1588  << o_names.at(i) << "\". Expected " << sp.size()
1589  << " but got " << ret.size_out(i));

1594

1931  }

1933  << " }" << endl

1938  return;
1939  }

1945  s << " case " << i << ": return s" << g.addSparsity(sparsity_in(i)) << ";" << endl;

1948  << " }" << endl

1958  << " }" << endl
1959  << "}" << endl << endl;

1962  s << g.declare("int " + fname + "_work(int *sz_arg, int* sz_res, int *sz_iw, int *sz_w)");
1963  s << " {" << endl;
1964  s << " if (sz_arg) *sz_arg = " << sz_arg() << ";" << endl;

1969  s << "}" << endl;
1970  s << endl;
1971

1973  if (g.mex) {

1975  s << "#ifdef MATLAB_MEX_FILE" << endl;
1976 
1977  // Declare wrapper
1978  s << "void mex_" << fname
1979  << "(int resc, mxArray *resv[], int argc, const mxArray *argv[]) {" << endl
1980  << " int i, j;" << endl;
1981 
1982  // Check arguments
1983  s << " if (argc>" << n_in << ") mexErrMsgIdAndTxt(\"Casadi:RuntimeError\","
1984  << "\"Evaluation of \\\"" << fname << "\\\" failed. Too many input arguments "
1985  << "(%d, max " << n_in << ")\", argc);" << endl;
1986 
1987  s << " if (resc>" << n_out << ") mexErrMsgIdAndTxt(\"Casadi:RuntimeError\","
1988  << "\"Evaluation of \\\"" << fname << "\\\" failed. "
1989  << "Too many output arguments (%d, max " << n_out << ")\", resc);" << endl;
1990 
1991  // Work vectors, including input and output buffers
1992  int i_nnz = nnz_in(), o_nnz = nnz_out();
1993  size_t sz_w = this->sz_w();
1994  for (int i=0; i<n_in; ++i) {
1995  const Sparsity& s = sparsity_in(i);
1996  sz_w = max(sz_w, static_cast<size_t>(s.size1())); // To be able to copy a column
1997  sz_w = max(sz_w, static_cast<size_t>(s.size2())); // To be able to copy a row
1998  }
1999  sz_w += i_nnz + o_nnz;
2000  s << " int iw[" << sz_iw() << "];" << endl;
2001  s << " real_t w[" << sz_w << "];" << endl;
2002  string fw = "w+" + g.to_string(i_nnz + o_nnz);
2003 
2004  // Copy inputs to buffers
2005  int offset=0;
2006  s << " const real_t* arg[" << n_in << "] = {0};" << endl;
2007  for (int i=0; i<n_in; ++i) {
2008  std::string p = "argv[" + g.to_string(i) + "]";
2009  s << " if (--argc>=0) arg[" << i << "] = "
2010  << g.from_mex(p, "w", offset, sparsity_in(i), fw) << endl;
2011  offset += nnz_in(i);
2012  }
2013 
2014  // Allocate output buffers
2015  s << " real_t* res[" << n_out << "] = {0};" << endl;
2016  for (int i=0; i<n_out; ++i) {
2017  if (i==0) {
2018  // if i==0, always store output (possibly ans output)
2019  s << " --resc;" << endl
2020  << " ";
2021  } else {
2022  // Store output, if it exists
2023  s << " if (--resc>=0) ";
2024  }
2025  // Create and get pointer
2026  s << "res[" << i << "] = w+" << g.to_string(offset) << ";" << endl;
2027  offset += nnz_out(i);
2028  }
2029 
2030  // Call the function
2031  s << " i = " << fname << "(arg, res, iw, " << fw << ", 0);" << endl;
2032  s << " if (i) mexErrMsgIdAndTxt(\"Casadi:RuntimeError\",\"Evaluation of \\\"" << fname
2033  << "\\\" failed.\");" << endl;
2034 
2035  // Save results
2036  for (int i=0; i<n_out; ++i) {
2037  string res_i = "res[" + g.to_string(i) + "]";
2038  s << " if (" << res_i << ") resv[" << i << "] = "
2039  << g.to_mex(sparsity_out(i), res_i) << endl;
2040  }
2041 
2042  // End conditional compilation and function
2043  s << "}" << endl
2044  << "#endif" << endl << endl;
2045  }
2046 
2047  if (g.main) {
2048  // Declare wrapper
2049  s << "int main_" << fname << "(int argc, char* argv[]) {" << endl;
2050

2052  size_t nr = sz_w() + nnz_in() + nnz_out();
2053  s << " int iw[" << sz_iw() << "];" << endl
2054  << " real_t w[" << nr << "];" << endl;

2060  if (i!=0) s << ", ";
2061  s << "w+" << off;
2062  off += nnz_in(i);
2063  }
2064  s << "};" << endl;
2065

2069  if (i!=0) s << ", ";
2070  s << "w+" << off;
2071  off += nnz_out(i);
2072  }
2073  s << "};" << endl;
2074

2076  s << " int j;" << endl
2077  << " real_t* a = w;" << endl
2078  << " for (j=0; j<" << nnz_in() << "; ++j) "
2079  << "scanf(\"%lf\", a++);" << endl;
2080 
2081  // Call the function

1084  fine_row.insert(fine_row.end(), temp.begin(), temp.end());
1085  }
1086  if (fine_row.back()!=coarse_row.back()) fine_row.push_back(coarse_row.back());
1087  if (fine_col.back()!=coarse_col.back()) fine_col.push_back(coarse_col.back());
1088 
1089  granularity_col = fine_col[1] - fine_col[0];
1090  granularity_row = fine_row[1] - fine_row[0];
1091 
1092  // The index into the bvec bit vector
1093  int bvec_i = 0;
1094 
1095  // Create lookup tables for the fine blocks
1096  std::vector<int> fine_col_lookup = lookupvector(fine_col, nz_sens+1);
1097  std::vector<int> fine_row_lookup = lookupvector(fine_row, nz_seed+1);
1098 
1099  // Triplet data used as a lookup table
1100  std::vector<int> lookup_col;
1101  std::vector<int> lookup_row;
1102  std::vector<int> lookup_value;
1103 
1104  // Loop over all coarse seed directions from the coloring
1105  for (int csd=0; csd<D.size2(); ++csd) {
1106 
1107  // The maximum number of fine blocks contained in one coarse block
1108  int n_fine_blocks_max = fine_row_lookup[coarse_row[1]]-fine_row_lookup[coarse_row[0]];
1109 
1110  int fci_offset = 0;
1111  int fci_cap = bvec_size-bvec_i;
1112 
1113  // Flag to indicate if all fine blocks have been handled
1114  bool f_finished = false;
1115 
1116  // Loop while not finished
1117  while (!f_finished) {
1118 
1119  // Loop over all coarse rows that are found in the coloring for this coarse seed direction
1120  for (int k=D.colind(csd); k<D.colind(csd+1); ++k) {
1121  int cci = D.row(k);
1122 
1123  // The first and last rows of the fine block
1124  int fci_start = fine_row_lookup[coarse_row[cci]];
1125  int fci_end = fine_row_lookup[coarse_row[cci+1]];
1126 
1127  // Local counter that modifies index into bvec
1128  int bvec_i_mod = 0;
1129 
1130  int value = -bvec_i + fci_offset + fci_start;
1131 
1132  // Loop over the rows of the fine block
1133  for (int fci = fci_offset; fci<min(fci_end-fci_start, fci_cap); ++fci) {
1134 
1135  // Loop over the coarse block cols that appear in the coloring
1136  // for the current coarse seed direction
1137  for (int cri=rT.colind(cci);cri<rT.colind(cci+1);++cri) {
1138  lookup_col.push_back(rT.row(cri));
1139  lookup_row.push_back(bvec_i+bvec_i_mod);
1140  lookup_value.push_back(value);
1141  }
1142 
1143  // Toggle on seeds
1144  bvec_toggle(seed_v, fine_row[fci+fci_start], fine_row[fci+fci_start+1],
1145  bvec_i+bvec_i_mod);
1146  bvec_i_mod++;
1147  }
1148  }
1149 
1150  // Bump bvec_i for next major coarse direction
1151  bvec_i+= min(n_fine_blocks_max, fci_cap);
1152 
1153  // Check if bvec buffer is full
1154  if (bvec_i==bvec_size || csd==D.size2()-1) {
1155  // Calculate sparsity for bvec_size directions at once
1156 
1157  // Statistics
1158  nsweeps+=1;
1159 
1160  // Construct lookup table
1161  IM lookup = IM::triplet(lookup_row, lookup_col, lookup_value, bvec_size,
1162  coarse_col.size());
1163 
1164  // Propagate the dependencies
1165  if (use_fwd) {
1166  spFwd(get_ptr(arg_fwd), get_ptr(res), get_ptr(iw), get_ptr(w), 0);
1167  } else {
1168  fill(w.begin(), w.end(), 0);
1169  spAdj(get_ptr(arg_adj), get_ptr(res), get_ptr(iw), get_ptr(w), 0);
1170  }
1171 
1172  // Temporary bit work vector
1173  bvec_t spsens;
1174 
1175  // Loop over the cols of coarse blocks
1176  for (int cri=0;cri<coarse_col.size()-1;++cri) {
1177 
1178  // Loop over the cols of fine blocks within the current coarse block
1179  for (int fri=fine_col_lookup[coarse_col[cri]];
1180  fri<fine_col_lookup[coarse_col[cri+1]];++fri) {
1181  // Lump individual sensitivities together into fine block
1182  bvec_or(sens_v, spsens, fine_col[fri], fine_col[fri+1]);
1183 
1184  // Next iteration if no sparsity
1185  if (!spsens) continue;
1186 
1187  // Loop over all bvec_bits
1188  for (int bvec_i=0;bvec_i<bvec_size;++bvec_i) {
1189  if (spsens & bvec_lookup[bvec_i]) {
1190  // if dependency is found, add it to the new sparsity pattern
1191  int ind = lookup.sparsity().get_nz(bvec_i, cri);
1192  if (ind==-1) continue;
1193  jrow.push_back(bvec_i+lookup->at(ind));
1194  jcol.push_back(fri);
1195  }
1196  }
1197  }
1198  }
1199 
1200  // Clear the forward seeds/adjoint sensitivities, ready for next bvec sweep
1201  fill(s_in.begin(), s_in.end(), 0);
1202 
1203  // Clear the adjoint seeds/forward sensitivities, ready for next bvec sweep
1204  fill(s_out.begin(), s_out.end(), 0);
1205 
1206  // Clean lookup table
1207  lookup_col.clear();
1208  lookup_row.clear();
1209  lookup_value.clear();
1210  }
1211 
1212  if (n_fine_blocks_max>fci_cap) {
1213  fci_offset += min(n_fine_blocks_max, fci_cap);
1214  bvec_i = 0;
1215  fci_cap = bvec_size;
1216  } else {
1217  f_finished = true;
1218  }
1219 
1220  }
1221 
1222  }
1223 
1224  // Swap results if adjoint mode was used
1225  if (use_fwd) {
1226  // Construct fine sparsity pattern
1227  r = Sparsity::triplet(fine_row.size()-1, fine_col.size()-1, jrow, jcol);
1228  coarse_col = fine_col;
1229  coarse_row = fine_row;
1230  } else {
1231  // Construct fine sparsity pattern
1232  r = Sparsity::triplet(fine_col.size()-1, fine_row.size()-1, jcol, jrow);
1233  coarse_col = fine_row;
1234  coarse_row = fine_col;
1235  }
1236  hasrun = true;
1237  }
1238  casadi_msg("Number of sweeps: " << nsweeps);
1239  casadi_msg("Formed Jacobian sparsity pattern (dimension " << r.size() <<
1240  ", " << r.nnz() << " nonzeros, " << (100.0*r.nnz())/r.numel() << " % nonzeros).");
1241 
1242  return r.T();
1243  }

1360  Sparsity &AT = sparsity_jac(iind, oind, compact, symmetric);

1365  casadi_assert(get_n_forward()>0);
1366

1368  log("FunctionInternal::getPartition star_coloring");

1370  casadi_msg("Star coloring completed: " << D1.size2() << " directional derivatives needed ("

1373  } else {
1374  casadi_assert(get_n_forward()>0 || get_n_reverse()>0);
1375  // Get weighting factor
1376  double w = adWeight();
1377 
1378  // Which AD mode?
1379  bool test_ad_fwd=w<1, test_ad_adj=w>0;
1380 
1381  // Best coloring encountered so far (relatively tight upper bound)
1382  double best_coloring = numeric_limits<double>::infinity();
1383 
1384  // Test forward mode first?
1385  bool test_fwd_first = test_ad_fwd && w*A.size1() <= (1-w)*A.size2();
1386  int mode_fwd = test_fwd_first ? 0 : 1;
1387 
1388  // Test both coloring modes
1389  for (int mode=0; mode<2; ++mode) {
1390  // Is this the forward mode?
1391  bool fwd = mode==mode_fwd;
1392 
1393  // Skip?
1394  if (!test_ad_fwd && fwd) continue;
1395  if (!test_ad_adj && !fwd) continue;
1396 
1397  // Perform the coloring
1398  if (fwd) {
1399  log("FunctionInternal::getPartition unidirectional coloring (forward mode)");
1400  int max_colorings_to_test = best_coloring>=w*A.size1() ? A.size1() :
1401  floor(best_coloring/w);
1402  D1 = AT.uni_coloring(A, max_colorings_to_test);
1403  if (D1.is_null()) {
1404  if (verbose()) userOut() << "Forward mode coloring interrupted (more than "
1405  << max_colorings_to_test << " needed)." << endl;
1406  } else {
1407  if (verbose()) userOut() << "Forward mode coloring completed: "
1408  << D1.size2() << " directional derivatives needed ("
1409  << A.size1() << " without coloring)." << endl;
1410  D2 = Sparsity();
1411  best_coloring = w*D1.size2();
1412  }
1413  } else {
1414  log("FunctionInternal::getPartition unidirectional coloring (adjoint mode)");
1415  int max_colorings_to_test = best_coloring>=(1-w)*A.size2() ? A.size2() :
1416  floor(best_coloring/(1-w));
1417 
1418  D2 = A.uni_coloring(AT, max_colorings_to_test);
1419  if (D2.is_null()) {
1420  if (verbose()) userOut() << "Adjoint mode coloring interrupted (more than "
1421  << max_colorings_to_test << " needed)." << endl;
1422  } else {

1427  best_coloring = (1-w)*D2.size2();
